hwWlanAp.name: hwWlanAp

revisions.description: V1.29, Add hwApSpecificConfigChangedTrap, hwApSpecificChangeConfig, hwApSpecificChangeReason and hwApSpecificChangeRadioID node.
V1.26, Add hwApVapStaFullTrap hwVapStaFullRecoverTrap and hwWlanApWlanID node.
V1.25, Add hwAPIoTCardInsertTrap hwAPIoTCardRemoveTrap hwAPIoTServerStartFailTrap hwAPIoTServerStartFailResumeTrap hwWlanApSubFirmwareMismatchTrap node.
V1.24, Add hwWlanApSDCardSize and hwWlanIDIndexedApSDCardSize node.
V1.13, Add the hwWlanApWiredPortApId and hwWlanApWiredPortApName node.
V1.09, Add the AP ID in the trap node.
V1.08, Modify the value of hwWlanApRunState.
V1.06, Add node of AP optical module Tx power.
V1.04, Add the description of mib nodes.
V1.03, Modify the sequence of table's index and the value of hwWlanApTypeRadioType.
V1.02, Modify the value of hwWlanApRunState.
V1.01, Modify the value of hwWlanApRunState.

hwApFaultTrap.name: hwApFaultTrap
hwApFaultTrap.description: The object indicates an AP communication fault alarm.

hwApNormalTrap.name: hwApNormalTrap
hwApNormalTrap.description: This object indicates an AP communication fault clear alarm.

hwApPingResultTrap.name: hwApPingResultTrap
hwApPingResultTrap.description: This object indicates an AP ping result alarm.

hwApConfigCommitTrap.name: hwApConfigCommitTrap
hwApConfigCommitTrap.description: This object indicates that the configuration of an AP is successfully committed.

hwUnAuthorizedApRecordExistTrap.name: hwUnAuthorizedApRecordExistTrap
hwUnAuthorizedApRecordExistTrap.description: This object indicates that unauthorized AP alarms exist.

hwUnAuthorizedApRecordClearTrap.name: hwUnAuthorizedApRecordClearTrap
hwUnAuthorizedApRecordClearTrap.description: This object indicates that unauthorized AP alarms are cleared.

hwApCpuOverloadRestoreTrap.name: hwApCpuOverloadRestoreTrap

hwApMemoryOverloadTrap.name: hwApMemoryOverloadTrap

hwApMemoryOverloadRestoreTrap.name: hwApMemoryOverloadRestoreTrap
hwApMemoryOverloadRestoreTrap.description: This object indicates that the memory usage of an AP restores to the allowed range.

hwApStaFullTrap.name: hwApStaFullTrap

hwApStaFullRecoverTrap.name: hwApStaFullRecoverTrap
hwApStaFullRecoverTrap.description: This object indicates that new STAs can associate with an AP.

hwAcDevicesSwitchTrap.name: hwAcDevicesSwitchTrap

hwDyingGaspTrap.name: hwDyingGaspTrap
hwDyingGaspTrap.description: This object indicates a dying gasp alarm.

hwApTemperatureTooLowTrap.name: hwApTemperatureTooLowTrap

hwApTemperatureTooLowRestoreTrap.name: hwApTemperatureTooLowRestoreTrap
hwApTemperatureTooLowRestoreTrap.description: This object indicates that the temperature restores to the normal range.

hwApTemperatureTooHighTrap.name: hwApTemperatureTooHighTrap

hwApTemperatureTooHighRestoreTrap.name: hwApTemperatureTooHighRestoreTrap

hwApOpticalRxPowerTooHighRestoreTrap.name: hwApOpticalRxPowerTooHighRestoreTrap
hwApOpticalRxPowerTooHighRestoreTrap.description: This object indicates that the receive power of an AP's optical module restores to the normal range.

hwApOpticalRxPowerTooLowTrap.name: hwApOpticalRxPowerTooLowTrap
hwApOpticalRxPowerTooLowTrap.description: This object indicates that the receive power of an AP's optical module is too low.

hwApOpticalRxPowerTooLowRestoreTrap.name: hwApOpticalRxPowerTooLowRestoreTrap
hwApOpticalRxPowerTooLowRestoreTrap.description: This object indicates that the receive power of an AP's optical module restores to the normal range.

hwApOpticalTemperatureTooHighTrap.name: hwApOpticalTemperatureTooHighTrap
hwApOpticalTemperatureTooHighTrap.description: This object indicates that the temperature of an AP's optical module is too high.

hwApOpticalTemperatureTooHighRestoreTrap.name: hwApOpticalTemperatureTooHighRestoreTrap
hwApOpticalTemperatureTooHighRestoreTrap.description: This object indicates that the temperature of an AP's optical module restores to the normal range.

hwApOpticalTemperatureTooLowTrap.name: hwApOpticalTemperatureTooLowTrap
hwApOpticalTemperatureTooLowTrap.description: This object indicates that the temperature of an AP's optical module is too low.

hwApOpticalTemperatureTooLowRestoreTrap.name: hwApOpticalTemperatureTooLowRestoreTrap
hwApOpticalTemperatureTooLowRestoreTrap.description: This object indicates that the temperature of an AP's optical module restores to the normal range.

hwApNotSupportCountryCodeTrap.name: hwApNotSupportCountryCodeTrap
hwApNotSupportCountryCodeTrap.description: This object indicates that the country code is not supported.

hwApColdBootTrap.name: hwApColdBootTrap
hwApColdBootTrap.description: This object indicates a cold restart alarm.

hwApColdBootRestoreTrap.name: hwApColdBootRestoreTrap
hwApColdBootRestoreTrap.description: This object indicates a cold restart clear alarm.

hwApHotBootTrap.name: hwApHotBootTrap
hwApHotBootTrap.description: This object indicates a hot restart alarm.

hwApHotBootRestoreTrap.name: hwApHotBootRestoreTrap
hwApHotBootRestoreTrap.description: This object indicates a hot restart clear alarm.

hwApCRCTooHighTrap.name: hwApCRCTooHighTrap
hwApCRCTooHighTrap.description: This object indicates a CRC error alarm.

hwApCRCTooHighRestoreTrap.name: hwApCRCTooHighRestoreTrap
hwApCRCTooHighRestoreTrap.description: This object indicates that CRC error alarms are cleared.

hwApConflictApNameTrap.name: hwApConflictApNameTrap
hwApConflictApNameTrap.description: This object indicates an alarm of AP name conflict.

hwApLicenseTrap.name: hwApLicenseTrap
hwApLicenseTrap.description: This object indicates an AP license resource exhaustion alarm.

hwApFmeaIICFaultTrap.name: hwApFmeaIICFaultTrap
hwApFmeaIICFaultTrap.description: This object indicates an FMEA IIC fault alarm.

hwApFmeaIICFaultRestoreTrap.name: hwApFmeaIICFaultRestoreTrap
hwApFmeaIICFaultRestoreTrap.description: This object indicates that the FMEA IIC fault alarm is cleared.

hwApFmeaPHYFaultTrap.name: hwApFmeaPHYFaultTrap
hwApFmeaPHYFaultTrap.description: This object indicates an FMEA PHY fault alarm.

hwApFmeaPHYFaultRestoreTrap.name: hwApFmeaPHYFaultRestoreTrap
hwApFmeaPHYFaultRestoreTrap.description: This object indicates that the FMEA PHY fault alarm is cleared.

hwApFmeaFaultTrap.name: hwApFmeaFaultTrap
hwApFmeaFaultTrap.description: This object indicates an FMEA fault alarm.

hwApFmeaFaultRestoreTrap.name: hwApFmeaFaultRestoreTrap
hwApFmeaFaultRestoreTrap.description: This object indicates that the FMEA fault alarm is cleared.

hwApOpticalInsertTrap.name: hwApOpticalInsertTrap
hwApOpticalInsertTrap.description: This object indicates an alarm that is generated when an optical module is installed.

hwApOpticalRemoveTrap.name: hwApOpticalRemoveTrap
hwApOpticalRemoveTrap.description: This object indicates an alarm generated due to installation of an optical module is cleared.

hwApReceivedInvalidArpNewTrap.name: hwApReceivedInvalidArpNewTrap
hwApReceivedInvalidArpNewTrap.description: This object indicates that invalid ARP packets are received.

hwApVersionMismatchTrap.name: hwApVersionMismatchTrap
hwApVersionMismatchTrap.description: This object indicates that the AP version and the AC version do not match.

hwRadioUploadRemoteCaptureFileTrap.name: hwRadioUploadRemoteCaptureFileTrap
hwRadioUploadRemoteCaptureFileTrap.description: This object indicates the alarm on the remote capture result upload result.

hwApOnLineNumExceedCardSpecTrap.name: hwApOnLineNumExceedCardSpecTrap
hwApOnLineNumExceedCardSpecTrap.description: This object indicates the number of online APs on the card has exceeded the maximum value.

hwApFanInvalidTrap.name: hwApFanInvalidTrap
hwApFanInvalidTrap.description: This object indicates a complete failure of a fan.

hwApFanInvalidRestoreTrap.name: hwApFanInvalidRestoreTrap
hwApFanInvalidRestoreTrap.description: This object indicates that the complete failure of a fan has been rectified.

hwApStorageDevRemoveTrap.name: hwApStorageDevRemoveTrap
hwApStorageDevRemoveTrap.description: This object indicates that the storage card is removed.

hwApStorageDevInsertTrap.name: hwApStorageDevInsertTrap
hwApStorageDevInsertTrap.description: This object indicates that the storage card is installed.

hwApPoePowerOffTrap.name: hwApPoePowerOffTrap
hwApPoePowerOffTrap.description: This object indicates that a port is powered off.

hwApPoePowerOnTrap.name: hwApPoePowerOnTrap
hwApPoePowerOnTrap.description: This object indicates that a port is powered on.

hwApPoePdConnectedTrap.name: hwApPoePdConnectedTrap
hwApPoePdConnectedTrap.description: This object indicates that a port detects a PD connected to it.

hwApPoePdDisconnectedTrap.name: hwApPoePdDisconnectedTrap
hwApPoePdDisconnectedTrap.description: This object indicates that a port detects disconnection of the attached PD.

hwApPoePdClassOvercurrentTrap.name: hwApPoePdClassOvercurrentTrap
hwApPoePdClassOvercurrentTrap.description: This object indicates that a port detects a PD whose current exceeds the threshold of the corresponding class.

hwApPoePdPriorityDifferentTrap.name: hwApPoePdPriorityDifferentTrap
hwApPoePdPriorityDifferentTrap.description: This object indicates that the priority configured on a port is different from the PD priority.

hwApPoePowerOverUtilizationThresholdTrap.name: hwApPoePowerOverUtilizationThresholdTrap
hwApPoePowerOverUtilizationThresholdTrap.description: This object indicates that the load power of a PoE slot exceeds the upper limit.

hwApPoePowerOverUtilizationThresholdRest.name: hwApPoePowerOverUtilizationThresholdRestoreTrap
hwApPoePowerOverUtilizationThresholdRest.description: This object indicates that the load power of a PoE slot has fallen below the upper limit.

hwApSTPAutoShutdownTrap.name: hwApSTPAutoShutdownTrap
hwApSTPAutoShutdownTrap.description: This object indicates that STP detected a loop and shut down the port based on configuration.

hwApSTPAutoShutdownRestoreTrap.name: hwApSTPAutoShutdownRestoreTrap
hwApSTPAutoShutdownRestoreTrap.description: This object indicates that the shutdown port has recovered.

hwApOpticalInvalidTrap.name: hwApOpticalInvalidTrap
hwApOpticalInvalidTrap.description: This object indicates that the optical transceiver does not work normally.

hwApOpticalInvalidRestoreTrap.name: hwApOpticalInvalidRestoreTrap
hwApOpticalInvalidRestoreTrap.description: This object indicates that the optical transceiver has restored.

hwApVapStaFullTrap.name: hwApVapStaFullTrap
hwApVapStaFullTrap.description: This object indicates that new STAs cannot associate with an VAP.

hwVapStaFullRecoverTrap.name: hwVapStaFullRecoverTrap
hwVapStaFullRecoverTrap.description: This object indicates that new STAs can associate with an VAP.

hwApConfigInconsistWithActualTrap.name: hwApConfigInconsistWithActualTrap
hwApConfigInconsistWithActualTrap.description: This alarm is generated when a the AP config is inconsistent with the actual attribute.

hwWlanCrcErrActual.name: hwWlanCrcErrActual
hwWlanCrcErrActual.description: CRC error alarm threshold value.The unit is 1/10000.

hwWlanApFaultID.name: hwWlanApFaultID
hwWlanApFaultID.description: This object indicates an FMEA fault alarm.

hwApPoePdPriority.name: hwApPoePdPriority
hwApPoePdPriority.description: This object identifies the PD priority.The default value is low.

hwApPoePortPriority.name: hwApPoePortPriority
hwApPoePortPriority.description: This object identifies the priority of an interface.The default value is low.

hwApPoeCurConsumPower.name: hwApPoeCurConsumPower
hwApPoeCurConsumPower.description: This object identifies the current consuming power.

hwApPoeConsumPowerThreshold.name: hwApPoeConsumPowerThreshold
hwApPoeConsumPowerThreshold.description: This object identifies the threshold of consuming power.

hwApFanIndex.name: hwApFanIndex
hwApFanIndex.description: This object identifies the id of fan.

hwApEntityPhysicalName.name: hwApEntityPhysicalName
hwApEntityPhysicalName.description: This object identifies the phisical name of entity name.

hwApStorageIndex.name: hwApStorageIndex
hwApStorageIndex.description: This object identifies the id of Storage.

hwApStorageName.name: hwApStorageName
hwApStorageName.description: This object identifies the name of Storage.

hwWlanApOpticalFaultID.name: hwWlanApOpticalFaultID
hwWlanApOpticalFaultID.description: This object identifies the error corde of the optical transceiver fault.

hwWlanApWlanID.name: hwWlanApWlanID
hwWlanApWlanID.description: This object identifies the Wlan Id of the Vap that has the max number of stations.

hwPowerOffReason.name: hwPowerOffReason
hwPowerOffReason.description: This object identifies the reason of power off.

hwApSpecificChangeConfig.name: hwApSpecificChangeConfig
hwApSpecificChangeConfig.description: This object identifies the config of change.

hwApSpecificChangeReason.name: hwApSpecificChangeReason
hwApSpecificChangeReason.description: This object identifies the reason of change config.

hwApInconsisitConfig.name: hwApInconsisitConfig
hwApInconsisitConfig.description: This object identifies the inconsistent config.

hwApConfigInconsisitReason.name: hwApConfigInconsisitReason
hwApConfigInconsisitReason.description: This object identifies the reason of inconsistent config.

hwWlanApTypeTable.name: hwWlanApTypeTable
hwWlanApTypeTable.description: This table is used to query attributes based on AP types and restart APs based on AP types.

hwWlanApTypeEntry.name: hwWlanApTypeEntry
hwWlanApTypeEntry.description: The index of this table is hwWlanApType.

hwWlanApType.name: hwWlanApType
hwWlanApType.description: This object indicates the AP type name. It is the index of the table.

hwWlanApTypeDesc.name: hwWlanApTypeDesc
hwWlanApTypeDesc.description: This object indicates description of an AP type.

hwWlanApTypeWiredPortNum.name: hwWlanApTypeWiredPortNum
hwWlanApTypeWiredPortNum.description: This object indicates the number of wired ports on APs of a certain type.

hwWlanApTypeRadioNum.name: hwWlanApTypeRadioNum
hwWlanApTypeRadioNum.description: This object indicates the number of radios on APs of a certain type.

hwWlanApTypeMaxStaNum.name: hwWlanApTypeMaxStaNum
hwWlanApTypeMaxStaNum.description: This object indicates the maximum number of access STAs on an AP of a certain type.

hwWlanApTypeReset.name: hwWlanApTypeReset
hwWlanApTypeReset.description: This object indicates that APs are restarted based on the AP type.

hwWlanApTypeRadioTable.name: hwWlanApTypeRadioTable
hwWlanApTypeRadioTable.description: This table is used to query radio-related attributes of APs of a certain type.

hwWlanApTypeRadioEntry.name: hwWlanApTypeRadioEntry
hwWlanApTypeRadioEntry.description: The indexes of this table are hwWlanApType and hwWlanApTypeRadioIndex.

hwWlanApTypeRadioIndex.name: hwWlanApTypeRadioIndex
hwWlanApTypeRadioIndex.description: This object indicates the radio index of APs of a certain type.

hwWlanApTypeRadioType.name: hwWlanApTypeRadioType
hwWlanApTypeRadioType.description: This object indicates the radio type of APs of a certain type.

hwWlanRadioMaxSpatialStreamsNum.name: hwWlanRadioMaxSpatialStreamsNum
hwWlanRadioMaxSpatialStreamsNum.description: This object indicates the maximum number of spatial streams of an AP radio.

hwWlanApTypeRadioAntennaGain.name: hwWlanApTypeRadioAntennaGain
hwWlanApTypeRadioAntennaGain.description: This object indicates that the antenna gain is configured according to the radio ID.

hwWlanApTypeWiredPortTable.name: hwWlanApTypeWiredPortTable
hwWlanApTypeWiredPortTable.description: This table is used to query wired interface attributes of APs of a certain type.

hwWlanApTypeWiredPortEntry.name: hwWlanApTypeWiredPortEntry
hwWlanApTypeWiredPortEntry.description: The indexes of this table are hwWlanApType and hwWlanApTypeWiredPortIndex.

hwWlanApTypeWiredPortIndex.name: hwWlanApTypeWiredPortIndex
hwWlanApTypeWiredPortIndex.description: This object indicates the index of an AP's wired interface. Numbering rule: port-index = port-type * 100 + port-number. For example, the indexes of a wall plate AP's GE0, eth0, and eth1 are 200 (2 * 100 + 0 = 200), 100 (1 * 100 + 0 = 100), and 101 (1 * 100 + 1 = 101) respectively.

hwWlanApTypeWiredPortType.name: hwWlanApTypeWiredPortType
hwWlanApTypeWiredPortType.description: This object indicates the type of an AP's wired interface.

hwWlanApTypeWiredPortName.name: hwWlanApTypeWiredPortName
hwWlanApTypeWiredPortName.description: This object indicates the name of a wired interface on APs of a certain type, for example, ethernet 0, ethernet 1, gigabit-ethernet 0, and eth-trunk 0.

hwWlanApPingApMac.name: hwWlanApPingApMac
hwWlanApPingApMac.description: This object specifies the MAC address in an AP ping operation. If the AP ID and MAC address are specified concurrently, the AP is pinged based on the MAC address.

hwWlanApPingAddress.name: hwWlanApPingAddress
hwWlanApPingAddress.description: This object indicates the domain name or IP address of the destination host.

hwWlanApPingCount.name: hwWlanApPingCount
hwWlanApPingCount.description: This object indicates the number of times ICMP ECHO-REQUEST packets are sent.Default value: 4.

hwWlanApPingPacketSize.name: hwWlanApPingPacketSize
hwWlanApPingPacketSize.description: This object indicates the length of an ECHO-REQUE.

hwWlanApPingWaitTime.name: hwWlanApPingWaitTime
hwWlanApPingWaitTime.description: This object indicates the time to wait before sending the next ICMP Request packet.Unit: ms Default value: 2000.

hwWlanApPingTimeOut.name: hwWlanApPingTimeOut
hwWlanApPingTimeOut.description: This object indicates the timeout period for an ECHO-RESPONSE after an ECHO-REQUEST is sent.Unit: ms Default value: 2000.

hwWlanApPingResultSuccessCount.name: hwWlanApPingResultSuccessCount
hwWlanApPingResultSuccessCount.description: This object indicates the number of successful AP ping operations. Only the result of the latest AP ping operation is kept.

hwWlanApPingResultFailureCount.name: hwWlanApPingResultFailureCount
hwWlanApPingResultFailureCount.description: This object indicates the number of AP ping operation failures. Only the result of the latest AP ping operation is kept.

hwWlanApPingResultAveResponseTime.name: hwWlanApPingResultAveResponseTime
hwWlanApPingResultAveResponseTime.description: This object indicates the average response time for an AP ping operation. Only the result of the latest AP ping operation is kept.Unit: ms.

hwWlanApPingResultMinResponseTime.name: hwWlanApPingResultMinResponseTime
hwWlanApPingResultMinResponseTime.description: This object indicates the minimum response time for an AP ping operation. Only the result of the latest AP ping operation is kept.Unit: ms.

hwWlanApPingResultMaxResponseTime.name: hwWlanApPingResultMaxResponseTime
hwWlanApPingResultMaxResponseTime.description: This object indicates the maximum response time for an AP ping operation. Only the result of the latest AP ping operation is kept.Unit: ms.

hwWlanApPingResultFlag.name: hwWlanApPingResultFlag
hwWlanApPingResultFlag.description: This object indicates the result of the AP ping operation.

hwWlanUnauthedApRecordTable.name: hwWlanUnauthedApRecordTable
hwWlanUnauthedApRecordTable.description: This table describes rogue AP records. Rogue APs are those whose MAC addresses and SNs are not in the whitelist and not confirmed after being discovered by the AC.

hwWlanUnauthedApRecordEntry.name: hwWlanUnauthedApRecordEntry
hwWlanUnauthedApRecordEntry.description: The index of this table is hwWlanUnauthedApRecordIndex.

hwWlanUnauthedApRecordIndex.name: hwWlanUnauthedApRecordIndex
hwWlanUnauthedApRecordIndex.description: This object indicates the index of a rogue AP record.

hwWlanUnauthedApType.name: hwWlanUnauthedApType
hwWlanUnauthedApType.description: This object indicates the type of a rogue AP.

hwWlanUnauthedApMacAddress.name: hwWlanUnauthedApMacAddress
hwWlanUnauthedApMacAddress.description: This object indicates the type of a rogue AP.

hwWlanUnauthedApSn.name: hwWlanUnauthedApSn
hwWlanUnauthedApSn.description: This object indicates the SN of a rogue AP.

hwWlanUnauthedApIpAddress.name: hwWlanUnauthedApIpAddress
hwWlanUnauthedApIpAddress.description: This object indicates the IP address of a rogue AP.

hwWlanUnauthedApRecordTime.name: hwWlanUnauthedApRecordTime
hwWlanUnauthedApRecordTime.description: This object indicates the time when a rogue AP is recorded.

hwWlanApTable.name: hwWlanApTable
hwWlanApTable.description: This table is used to add, delete, modify, reset, or confirm APs. You can also use the table to query the configuration and restore factory settings of APs.

hwWlanApEntry.name: hwWlanApEntry
hwWlanApEntry.description: The index of this table is hwWlanApMac.

hwWlanApMac.name: hwWlanApMac
hwWlanApMac.description: This object indicates the MAC address of an AP.

hwWlanApSn.name: hwWlanApSn
hwWlanApSn.description: This object indicates the sequence number (SN) of an AP.

hwWlanApTypeInfo.name: hwWlanApTypeInfo
hwWlanApTypeInfo.description: This object indicates the AP type.

hwWlanApName.name: hwWlanApName
hwWlanApName.description: This object indicates the AP name.

hwWlanApGroup.name: hwWlanApGroup
hwWlanApGroup.description: This object indicates the group to which an AP belongs.

hwWlanApRunState.name: hwWlanApRunState
hwWlanApRunState.description: This object indicates the AP state.

hwWlanApSoftwareVersion.name: hwWlanApSoftwareVersion
hwWlanApSoftwareVersion.description: This object indicates the AP software version.

hwWlanApHardwareVersion.name: hwWlanApHardwareVersion
hwWlanApHardwareVersion.description: This object indicates the AP hardware version.

hwWlanApCpuType.name: hwWlanApCpuType
hwWlanApCpuType.description: This object indicates the CPU type of an AP.

hwWlanApCpufrequency.name: hwWlanApCpufrequency
hwWlanApCpufrequency.description: This object indicates the CPU frequency of an AP.Unit: MHz.

hwWlanApMemoryType.name: hwWlanApMemoryType
hwWlanApMemoryType.description: This object indicates the memory type of an AP.

hwWlanApDomain.name: hwWlanApDomain
hwWlanApDomain.description: This object indicates the AP domain.

hwWlanApIpAddress.name: hwWlanApIpAddress
hwWlanApIpAddress.description: This object indicates the IP address of an AP.

hwWlanApIpNetMask.name: hwWlanApIpNetMask
hwWlanApIpNetMask.description: This object indicates the IP address mask of an AP.

hwWlanApGatewayIp.name: hwWlanApGatewayIp
hwWlanApGatewayIp.description: This object indicates the gateway IP address of an AP.

hwWlanApMemorySize.name: hwWlanApMemorySize
hwWlanApMemorySize.description: This object indicates the memory size of an AP.Unit: MB.

hwWlanApFlashSize.name: hwWlanApFlashSize
hwWlanApFlashSize.description: This object indicates the flash memory size of an AP.Unit: MB.

hwWlanApRunTime.name: hwWlanApRunTime
hwWlanApRunTime.description: This object indicates the running time of an AP.Unit: tick.

hwWlanApAdminOper.name: hwWlanApAdminOper
hwWlanApAdminOper.description: This object indicates administrative status of an AP.

hwWlanApDNS.name: hwWlanApDNS
hwWlanApDNS.description: This object indicates the AP DNS.

hwWlanApOnlineTime.name: hwWlanApOnlineTime
hwWlanApOnlineTime.description: This object indicates online duration of an AP.

hwWlanApSysSoftwareDesc.name: hwWlanApSysSoftwareDesc
hwWlanApSysSoftwareDesc.description: This object indicates system software description of an AP.

hwWlanApSysHardtwareDesc.name: hwWlanApSysHardtwareDesc
hwWlanApSysHardtwareDesc.description: This object indicates system hardware description of an AP.

hwWlanApSysManufacture.name: hwWlanApSysManufacture
hwWlanApSysManufacture.description: This object indicates the manufacturer of an AP.

hwWlanApSysSoftwareName.name: hwWlanApSysSoftwareName
hwWlanApSysSoftwareName.description: This object indicates software name of an AP.

hwWlanApSysSoftwareVendor.name: hwWlanApSysSoftwareVendor
hwWlanApSysSoftwareVendor.description: This object indicates the manufacturer of the AP software.

hwWlanApBomCode.name: hwWlanApBomCode
hwWlanApBomCode.description: This object indicates the BOM code.

hwWlanApIpv6Address.name: hwWlanApIpv6Address
hwWlanApIpv6Address.description: This object indicates the IPv6 address.

hwWlanApIpv6NetMask.name: hwWlanApIpv6NetMask
hwWlanApIpv6NetMask.description: This object indicates the IPv6 address mask.

hwWlanApGatewayIpv6.name: hwWlanApGatewayIpv6
hwWlanApGatewayIpv6.description: This object indicates the IPv6 gateway.

hwWlanApIpv6DNS.name: hwWlanApIpv6DNS
hwWlanApIpv6DNS.description: This object indicates the IPv6 DNS.

hwWlanApProtectAcIPv6Addr.name: hwWlanApProtectAcIPv6Addr
hwWlanApProtectAcIPv6Addr.description: This object indicates the IPv6 address of the standby AC.

hwWlanApBootCountTotal.name: hwWlanApBootCountTotal
hwWlanApBootCountTotal.description: This object indicates the total number of times an AP is restarted.

hwWlanApBootCountPowerOff.name: hwWlanApBootCountPowerOff
hwWlanApBootCountPowerOff.description: This object indicates the number of times an AP is restarted due to a power failure.

hwWlanApBootCountClear.name: hwWlanApBootCountClear
hwWlanApBootCountClear.description: This object clears the AP restart count.

hwWlanApElectronicLabel.name: hwWlanApElectronicLabel
hwWlanApElectronicLabel.description: This object indicates the electronic label of an AP.

hwWlanApWiredPortNum.name: hwWlanApWiredPortNum
hwWlanApWiredPortNum.description: This object indicates the total number of wired interfaces.

hwWlanApWiredPortMtu.name: hwWlanApWiredPortMtu
hwWlanApWiredPortMtu.description: This object indicates the maximum transmit unit (MTU) of a wired interface.
